y. Decreased SIRT1 levels can lead to enhanced NF-&kappa;B activity, potentially due to the loss of SIRT1-mediated deacetylation and inhibition of NF-&kappa;B transcriptional activity.  This KER underscores the intricate interplay between proteins and signaling pathways within the cell, where changes in the levels of one protein, like SIRT1, can impact downstream signaling and cellular responses. The reduction in SIRT1 levels can contribute to heightened NF-&kappa;B activity, which in turn may influence various cellular processes, including inflammation, immune responses, and stress-related pathways.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:43:54 +0000 2026"}